# Rocketship BEM and SCSS Conventions

- **BEM block naming**
  - Use `rs` as the global block prefix to avoid clashes, e.g.:
    - `.rs-button`, `.rs-button__icon`, `.rs-button--primary`
    - `.rs-link`, `.rs-link__icon`, `.rs-link--muted`
  - Elements use `__`, modifiers use `--` exactly as in classic BEM.

- **Class responsibilities**
  - Blocks are reusable components (e.g. `rs-button`, `rs-container`).
  - Elements are structural parts of a block (e.g. `rs-button__label`, `rs-card__media`).
  - Modifiers represent visual/behavioral variants (e.g. `rs-button--secondary`, `rs-button--outline`).

- **Variables files (e.g. `variables.scss`)**
  - Must **never** contain class selectors (or any selectors other than `:root` and `@media`).
  - Only define CSS custom properties on `:root` and inside `@media (prefers-color-scheme: …)`. Component-specific tokens and class-based overrides belong in the component that owns them.

- **SCSS usage**
  - Prefer SCSS for authoring styles; compile to CSS for consumers.
  - **Use SCSS nesting** under the block: express BEM with `&__element` and `&--modifier` nested inside `.rs-block { ... }` instead of repeating full class names or writing flat unrelated selectors. Keep depth shallow (block → elements/modifiers only; avoid long descendant chains).
  - Use mixins and SCSS variables as needed, but **CSS custom properties** remain the public API for theming.
  - Component styles must be written directly inside the Astro component in a `<style lang="scss">` block.
  - Do not create separate component `.scss` files when the style belongs to a single component.
  - Use `media-breakpoint-up` only in Container/layout styles; use container queries for component/typography size changes.
  - Use `to-rem($px)` from `mixins/functions.scss` for every `font-size` authored in SCSS (design-token `--rs-font-size-*`, component fallbacks, body copy in `base.scss`, etc.), so sizes are defined from px and emitted as `rem`. Typography mixins already use `to-rem()`. Exception: print styles may use `pt` where appropriate.
  - Use `px` for all other dimensional values (including spacing, radii, layout dimensions, container-query thresholds, viewport breakpoints, letter-spacing, underline offsets, and underline thickness).

- **Declaration order (per rule block)**
  - **CSS custom properties (`--rs-*`) always first** in the block.
  - Then reset if needed (e.g. `all: unset` for buttons/controls), then `box-sizing` if you reset.
  - Then all other properties (layout, appearance, etc.).

- **CSS variable conventions**
  - All design tokens and component-level variables exposed to users should be named with the `--rs-*` prefix, for example:
    - `--rs-color-bg`, `--rs-color-fg`
    - `--rs-color-accent`, `--rs-color-border`
    - `--rs-font-family-sans`, `--rs-font-size-md`
    - `--rs-space-sm`, `--rs-radius-md`
  - Component-specific variables should still follow the `--rs-*` prefix and clearly indicate scope (e.g. `--rs-button-bg`, `--rs-button-border-radius`).
  - **Prefer chaining variables over repeating properties after mixins:** typography heading mixins use `--rs-heading-spacing-top` and `--rs-heading-spacing-bottom` (see `mixins/typography/headings.scss`). In a component, set those tokens—or define a component token (e.g. `--rs-block-title-spacing-bottom`) and assign it **into** the mixin’s inputs (`--rs-heading-spacing-bottom: var(--rs-block-title-spacing-bottom)`)—instead of `@include typography-h2` plus separate `margin-top` / `margin-bottom` declarations that duplicate what the mixin already drives from variables.

- **No inline styles for design**
  - Do not use inline `style="..."` attributes for anything related to design or theming.
  - Use classes + `--rs-*` variables instead so themes and consumers can override styles cleanly.

- **Selector style**
  - Prefer class-based selectors; avoid element-tag or ID-based styling in reusable components.
  - Rely on BEM + SCSS nesting (`&__` / `&--`) rather than deep ad hoc descendant selectors.

